##6.5 million merchants'life-and-death rescue

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

The epidemic of e-commerce business, there is no "things slow round. ".

If you don't get 800,000 yuan from Taobao ahead of time, or more than 200,000 yuan from the Cash advance, Wuhan businessman Jiao Chinan's six-year-old children's shoe business "will last only ten days. " The company's Operations Division also has 50 Wuhan Employees "crying out for work. ".

Everything can wait for the snow to melt and grow toward the Sun, but for China's more than 40 million small and medium-sized enterprises, every second that cash runs out is a matter of life and death.

As an entrepreneur, BA man noodles founder Zhang Tianyi can feel more "by cash flow choking throat" of the urgency. On the eve of the epidemic, the company is opening a new store, more than 60 offline stores, a month of nearly 20 million yuan in cost expenditure, coupled with wages day is getting closer and closer, Zhang Tianyi prepared for the worst: Ammunition Out of food, also three or four months.

It is in the 15-day "survival point" , 6.6 million Yuan Taobao back, saved Zhang Tianyi and Baman's emergency.

"The poor are easy to pass, poor business is sad, " said Li Ka Shing, who has been at the mall all his life. "In difficult times, poor families can still economize and make ends meet, but "poor business is hard, very hard. ".

The good news is that the 6.5 million Taobao tmall merchants are not alone.

Corporate death line

Sudden Epidemic Situation, let Jiao Chi Nan can not go home, more "can not go back to blood. ".

A year ago, Jiao Zhinan could not avoid "bleeding" : nearly 180 employees received year-end bonuses and vacation pay totaling 1 million yuan; in 2020, nearly 3 million yuan was spent on the design and production of new products in spring and summer; and in factory and warehouse rentals, nearly 1.3 million yuan was spent, together with the 500,000 yuan paid to the supplier... Total zero, the company spent nearly 6 million yuan before the Spring Festival.

In 2014, Chiao founded Lala pig, a children's shoe brand, with partners to build their own factory in Jinhua, Zhejiang Province, while operating the "Lala pig flagship store" on tmall. Six years, "Lala pig" annual production and sales value of 60 million to 80 million yuan. As a native of Wuhan, Chiao put the company's operations department in his hometown, more than 50 employees are also basically Wuhan, Hubei People.

Before the outbreak, Jiao was already feeling the pinch: "there was a lot of pressure behind it years ago. " Jinhua's factory rents a year, up 40 percent from last year. "The demand for development and new products is also quite big, so the funds are all spent. ". Jiao, who had been preparing for a loan of 700,000 to 1 million yuan, applied to the bank around January 16. "I didn't feel anything about the epidemic at that time, and I went to work normally, " he said, but "I didn't expect this. ".

The loan application dragged on for weeks and weeks. "The bank didn't give an answer for two weeks, and by the third week there was no way to get it done. " While waiting, he took his wife and children on vacation to Thailand, but when they returned home, the city was closed and the family had to "defect" to their partners in Jinhua, while their parents stayed in Wuhan.

For the people of Wuhan, it is destined to be an unforgettable Spring Festival, and Jiao Chi Nan is no exception. However, he still has a layer of pressure to survive until the seventh day of the first lunar month, and it is still a long way off for him to resume his full work, there were 20% of the original inventory is off-line wholesale channels, the epidemic period is simply not moving, the company has nearly 4 million yuan loan to pay, the loan has not been heard from..

Can Not wait any longer, February 3, Jiao Chi Nan from the credit card cash 200,000 yuan or so emergency, but "do platform promotion is not enough, can only support a 10 days. "

Anxiety and stress, Zhang Tianyi did not taste less.

After the outbreak of the disease, most of the 60-plus stores of Baman Rice noodle had their "income reduced to zero" , and the time for patrolling the stores was greatly reduced. However, working from home still kept the original work schedule. After getting up at 6 a.m. , think for two hours: "This time to rack your brains, more dead brain cells, perhaps the company will be a little more alive. "

At the beginning of 2020, Zhang tian-yi was full of ambition and posted a message to his friends: "starting from today, a new store will be opened every day until the end of the year. " In the past year, the five-year-old Baman Rice noodle has entered a period of rapid development, as originally planned, at the end of 2019 and the beginning of 2020, zhang is opening more than a dozen new stores in Beijing and Tianjin.

More than a month later, "if I could travel back to the end of the 19th year, I would never make the decision to open more than a dozen new stores by the end of the year, " Zhang wrote in "28 days of E-commerce for a restaurant company. ".

The opening of the new store put the brakes on the car, but the fixed expenditure of nearly 20 million yuan a month left Zhang breathless, "because we opened the store so quickly years ago, there was still a lot of money on the books, so when the epidemic hit, we weren't really in a well-funded situation. "

According to Zhang Tianyi worst estimate, "if the E-COMMERCE did not improve, not this piece of revenue to fill back, according to Revenue Participation Budget 0 situation, 3,4 months, the company almost not. "

Since starting his own business in 2014, "post-90s" Zhang Tianyi, a graduate of Peking University, has always been a well-known "start-up star" , ba Man Rice noodles has also grown into a chain restaurant brand with mature e-commerce operation experience, more than 500 employees and an annual turnover of over 400 million yuan. However, under the influence of the epidemic, these figures are both achievements and pressures, "More than 500 employees, each employee is behind a family. ".

Near the middle of February, the day of pay day approaching, Zhang Tianyi's most anxious moment came, "labor, rent expenses, and no income, in fact from February 10 to the end of February, this time period is the 'survival point. "

"Help" 0 accounting period

The experiences of Chiao chi-nan and Zhang Tianyi are the epitome of tens of millions of small and medium-sized enterprises, start-ups and Taobao tmall merchants under the epidemic.

In a recent survey of 995 small and medium-sized enterprises conducted jointly by Tsinghua University and Peking University, the results showed that 29.58 percent of the enterprises affected by the epidemic saw their revenue drop by more than 50 percent in 2020, and 58.05 percent by more than 20 percent, 85.01% of businesses don't survive for three months.

"Cash is oxygen, and 99% of the time you don't pay attention to it until it's gone, " Buffett says of cash flow, an unexpected reflection of the state of SME survival in an epidemic.

And for small and micro enterprises, to give the money on the "a little sunshine" , it is enough to "brilliant. ".

In a recent survey of small and micro businesses, Alibaba found that the top three factors affecting its costs were rent, labor and loan interest, as well as factors such as the backlog of raw materials and the cost of default, among them, 96% of the small and micro operators have a capital gap of less than 1 million yuan. Chairman of the Board Jang Yong, Alibaba's chief executive officer, called for small businesses to be able to weather the storm with a little support at the Hangzhou War Disease Promotion and Development Conference on March 2.

Just as businesses were running out of time, money came to the rescue.

It is understood that e-commerce platform's payback cycle is usually 15 to 45 days, or even longer, Zhang Tianyi admitted that under the epidemic, "these 15 days are critical to us. ". At the same time, tmall business operation experts also said that the epidemic has affected many businesses on the platform. Through collecting business operation difficulties, we found that the biggest pain point is because of slow logistics, accounting period has been stretched, resulting in cash flow disruption. Survey data shows that 80% of small and medium-sized businesses there is a shortage of funds, 70% said at the same time, as long as the money chain, there is confidence in business recovery.

On February 10, Zhang Tianyi, who browses the information of various cooperation platforms every day, found that Taobao had launched a free "zero account period" service. He contacted the company's Financial Department immediately to apply for the service.

One day later, people in a foreign country of Chiao Chinan also found Taobao Free "0 Account Period" service, without a second thought, he also immediately applied.

Zhang Tianyi and Jiao Chi Nan all said that the free "0 Account Period" application is very convenient, "not too much trouble to declare procedures" , the seller log in the background a little bit, the application was successful, after the shipment, the account can be quickly received.

"Early Collection allows merchants to apply to online commercial banks for advance payment of goods in transit, without affecting the secured transaction model, and further shorten the account period to zero, " said Zhang Kaifu, a member of Alibaba's merchants support group and head of Taobao's Industry Platform Division, in this process, consumers are still protected by secured transactions, merchants can immediately cash for production and operation, which capital costs and risks by Taobao platform and the bank fully bear.

It is reported that the service will be provided free of charge until March 31, during which the bank will pay 50-100 billion of capital lending. Taobao tmall in the 10 major business-oriented initiatives, free "0 Account Period" service is the first domestic e-commerce platform.

Zhang Tianyi said that after applying for the Free 0 Account Period Service, BA man received more than 2 million yuan in the first time accumulated in the TMALL "Ba man food flagship store, " in the most anxious moment, "we suddenly eased over. ". By March, BA man had withdrawn about 6.6 million yuan in cash.

Chiao chi-nan also breathed a sigh of relief. With the support of the Free 0 account period, 800,000 yuan of money flowed back into his bank account. Now, he sells and delivers goods in the amount of 80,000-120,000 yuan every day. "If you deliver goods, you will receive money back. " It is expected that 1 million yuan will be repaid in advance in March, has Greatly eased the company's cash crunch.

It is understood that Taobao launched a free "zero account period" , the average seller account period shortened by 7.5 days.

At the same time, alipay issued an initiative to Taobao buyers to "confirm receipt of goods. " The initiative said, "If the merchants receive the money one minute earlier, they will have a chance of surviving. " In addition, the bank has also launched a special loan of 10 billion yuan at a 20% interest rate to help 300,000 merchants resume work and production.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"msmes are responsible for a lot of jobs in China and after the epidemic, liquidity and cash flow have a bearing on their survival. As Li Haitao, a finance professor and Associate Dean at the Cheung Kong Graduate School of Business, puts it: Taobao Free 0 Account Service and E-commerce Bank's financial support practices, is "the platform to sacrifice their short-term interests" , "precision drip irrigation, bringing stability and development of millions of small and medium-sized micro enterprises

Zhang Tianyi, who recovered from the accident, quickly used the money back to carry out the reproduction and marketing of instant rice noodle products. On the live broadcast on February 28 in cooperation with the anchor via, BA man sold 3 million yuan of half-finished instant rice noodles in one night. Zhang Tianyi said that in 2017, the company saw the future of food retailing and began to develop and launch semi-finished instant rice noodles. In the special moment of the epidemic, instant food products and the Free 0 billing period "are a perfect combination, " "it's saved our lives. " IN-STORE TAKEOUT is back to 30% of what it was.

Due to the shortage of manpower, now, Jiao Chinan is busy packing and delivering goods every day. There are still more than 200,000 pairs of children's shoes available for sale in the library. Nearly eight million yuan of children's shoes are available for sale. The money-back money is also quickly used by Jiao Chinan for normal continuous operations, "such as delivering goods. " At the same time, production of children's shoes began to resume gradually at the Jinhua factory, and the money collected was mainly used for materials, labor and basic expenses.

For Jiao Chinan in the cold winter, although the upstream raw material shortage, labor shortage and other factors, production recovery is still very limited, but at least reproduction "can advance a little" to ensure sustainable operation of the company, "there is demand and there is supply, so there is no money problem. "
